The paper deals with designing data structures for curves in metric spaces, which is a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The focus is on distance oracles and nearest-neighbor data structures, which are also relevant to databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
